<font color="#FF0000">CLEAN IT UP!</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 20 16:13:13 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Big guns rattled the windows in the DVQ all night long!<br>
I could hardly concentrate on my newest Top Secret weapon designed for the Middle East.  May have to call in Dented Zippo for consultation.  Delivering bars of soap via 8 inch rounds is a little tricky.  Can you imagine the casualties incurred as Rag Heads flee a bar of soap dropped in their midst.  The stampede would kill millions.  We could call it a &quot;Clean Up&quot; operation without misrepresenting ourselves,as we usually do!<br>
The principle hangup is determining what kind of soap to use!<br><br>
Cookie recommends soap on a rope, the kind that you wear around your neck.. has a morbid fear of dropping soap in the shower..has something to do with serving in the Corps.<br><br>
Tom recommends lye soap..made in Tennessee.. too strong..would eat up the bores on the big guns and may cause casualties among the munitions handlers (Also smells worse than an Iraqi.. I fear they might like the stuff!<br><br>
Tunnel Rat, Toon Sarge and Green Grunt were no help at all.. they never heard of soap.<br><br>
Ditto..Army Aviators.. too cool..s**t don't stink.. never break a sweat..don't need soap!<br><br>
John wants to use Ivory..because it floats on top of the water.  He must have gotten water on the brain..it froze up and everything slipped off his mind.  There ain't no water in Bagdad!<br><br>
Silent Warrior was no help either.  His idea of bubble bath is to eat a couple pounds of pinto beans and sit in a tub of hot water... claims that Tide makes the biggest bubbles.<br><br>
Oh well, there goes another great plan for lack of support!<br><br>
MTF<br><br>

